    "attributes": {
        "action": "Amend the Overseas Operations Bill. Remove triple lock in cases of torture",
        "additional_details": "British forces should lead on human rights, not get involved in abuses we all oppose.\r\nTorture has been illegal in the UK for over 300 years.\r\nThe Government's position on torture has always been very clear. We unreservedly condemn its use as a matter of fundamental principle. The UK is committed to combating torture globally, and continues to implement an active campaign to help eradicate it.\r\n",
        "background": "Amend the Overseas Operations Bill to remove the \u201ctriple lock\u201d against prosecutions and ensure that those who commit torture, war crimes and crimes against humanity can be held accountable in the UK.",
